Travis Rebuilder

Usage
=====

Use this script to trigger a rebuild of all of the repositories in a travis
account.

This is usefull in order to test if all the repositories are working correctly
with latests upstream changes.

In order to make this script work, you should be logged to travis.
You can do this with the following command:

    travis login

Note: This commands require the travis-cli command installed. You can install
it with:

    gem install travis --no-rdoc --no-ri

Once you have installed the dependencies you can run the command with:

    rebuid_repositories.sh <username>

Changing <username> with the username you want to rebuild the repos.

Note the script will skip all the repositories which are currently build or
have been build today.
